20Trump%20has%20floated%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20three%20months%2C%20the%20CEOs%20and%20CFOs%20of%20public%20companies%20repeat%20a%20familiar%20process%3A%20They%20begin%20preparing%20to%20disclose%20their%20quarterly%20earnings%20to%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20wants%20that%20cadence%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Truth%20Social%20post%20on%20Monday%2C%20Trump%20said%20that%20US%20companies%20should%20be%20able%20to%20report%20their%20earnings%20every%20six%20months%2C%20not%20every%20three%20months%20as%20currently%20required%20by%20the%20SEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20will%20save%20money%2C%20and%20allow%20managers%20to%20focus%20on%20properly%20running%20their%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%20his%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.com%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.com%2F%40realDonaldTrump%2F115208219886830624%2Fembed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDid%20you%20ever%20hear%20the%20statement%20that%2C%20'China%20has%20a%2050%20to%20100%20year%20view%20on%20management%20of%20a%20company%2C%20whereas%20we%20run%20our%20companies%20on%20a%20quarterly%20basis%3F%3F%3F'%20Not%20good!!!%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20lengthening%20the%20earnings%20report%20cycle%20in%20his%20first%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202018%20post%20on%20what%20was%20then%20Twitter%2C%20Trump%20said%20he%20had%20heard%20from%20business%20leaders%20that%20semi-annual%20earnings%20reports%20would%20help%20them%20save%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20speaking%20with%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20top%20business%20leaders%20I%20asked%20what%20it%20is%20that%20would%20make%20business%20(jobs)%20even%20better%20in%20the%20U.S.%20'Stop%20quarterly%20reporting%20%26amp%3B%20go%20to%20a%20six%20month%20system%2C'%20said%20one.%20That%20would%20allow%20greater%20flexibility%20%26amp%3B%20save%20money.%20I%20have%20asked%20the%20SEC%20to%20study!%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%202018.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20SEC%20never%20implemented%20the%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20requirement%20for%20publicly%20traded%20companies%20to%20report%20quarterly%20earnings%20goes%20back%20to%201970%2C%20when%20the%20SEC%20made%20it%20a%20requirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22319c3603-84fb-4278-8abc-7089e5fe8e2d%5C%22%3ECEOs%20have%20publicly%20criticized%20the%20short-term%20focus%20of%20quarterly%20earnings%20%E2%80%94%20and%20guidance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExecutives%20from%20Elon%20Musk%20to%20Larry%20Fink%20to%20James%20Gorman%20have%20criticized%20various%20elements%20of%20the%20quarterly%20reporting%20requirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProponents%20of%20lengthening%20the%20reporting%20cadence%20say%20transitioning%20to%20a%20twice-a-year%20requirement%20would%20let%20companies%20focus%20more%20on%20long-term%20performance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mccombs.utexas.edu%2Fresearch%2Fwhats-the-frequency-quarterly-reporting-aids-investors%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdvocates%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20current%20quarterly%20requirement%20say%20that%20it%20gives%20investors%20more%20information%20and%20leads%20to%20fairer%20pricing%20of%20a%20company's%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BToday's%20culture%20of%20quarterly%20earnings%20hysteria%20is%20totally%20contrary%20to%20the%20long-term%20approach%20we%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20BlackRock%20CEO%20Larry%20Fink%20wrote%20in%20his%202016%20letter%20to%20shareholders.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20clear%2C%20we%20do%20believe%20companies%20should%20still%20report%20quarterly%20results%20%E2%80%94%20'long-termism'%20should%20not%20be%20a%20substitute%20for%20transparency%20%E2%80%94%20but%20CEOs%20should%20be%20more%20focused%20in%20these%20reports%20on%20demonstrating%20progress%20against%20their%20strategic%20plans%20than%20a%20one-penny%20deviation%20from%20their%20EPS%20targets%20or%20analyst%20consensus%20estimates%2C%26quot%3B%20Fink%20wrote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-warren-buffett-spends-money-net-worth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWarren%20Buffett%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Jamie%20Dimon%20criticized%20%26quot%3Bshort-termism%26quot%3B%20in%20a%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fshort-termism-is-harming-the-economy-1528336801%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-ed%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20and%20encouraged%20public%20companies%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Econsider%20moving%20away%20from%20providing%20quarterly%20earnings-per-share%20guidance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BOur%20views%20on%20quarterly%20earnings%20forecasts%20should%20not%20be%20misconstrued%20as%20opposition%20to%20quarterly%20and%20annual%20reporting%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20two%20business%20leaders%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BTransparency%20about%20financial%20and%20operating%20results%20is%20an%20essential%20aspect%20of%20US%20public%20markets%2C%20and%20we%20support%20being%20open%20with%20shareholders%20about%20actual%20financial%20and%20operational%20metrics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-wants-company-earnings-change-6-months-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757941480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c80f50183847aa39d6c1b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ftrump-wants-company-earnings-change-6-months-2025-9%22%2C%22su